To simplify \(-\frac{44}{55}\), factor out the greatest common divisor of 44 and 55, which is 11:

\[
-\frac{44}{55}
= -\frac{11\cdot 4}{11\cdot 5}
= -\frac{4}{5}.
\]

First factor everything:

\[
\frac{3s^2}{s^2-16}\;\div\;\frac{s^3+4s^2+16s}{\,s^3-64\,}
=
\frac{3s^2}{(s-4)(s+4)}
\;\times\;
\frac{s^3-64}{s(s^2+4s+16)}.
\]

But
  • \(s^3-64=(s-4)(s^2+4s+16)\),  
  • \(s^3+4s^2+16s=s\,(s^2+4s+16)\).

So the product becomes

\[
\frac{3s^2}{(s-4)(s+4)}
\;\times\;
\frac{(s-4)(s^2+4s+16)}{s\,(s^2+4s+16)}
\;=\;
\frac{3s^2}{\cancel{(s-4)}\,(s+4)}
\;\times\;
\frac{\cancel{(s-4)}\,\cancel{(s^2+4s+16)}}{s\,\cancel{(s^2+4s+16)}}
\;=\;
\frac{3s^2}{s\,(\,s+4\,)}
=\frac{3s}{s+4}\,. 
\]

Final answer:
\[
\boxed{\frac{3s}{s+4},}
\]
with the understanding that the original expression is undefined at 
\[
s=4,\;-4,\;0
\]
(these make one of the original denominators zero).

First rewrite the division as a multiplication by the reciprocal and factor everything you can:

\[
\frac{p^3+q^3}{3(p^2+pq+q^2)} \;\div\; \frac{p^2-q^2}{12}
\;=\;
\frac{p^3+q^3}{3(p^2+pq+q^2)}\;\times\;\frac{12}{\,p^2-q^2\,}.
\]

Now use the sums‐and‐differences of cubes and squares:

1. \(p^3+q^3=(p+q)(p^2-pq+q^2)\).  
2. \(p^2-q^2=(p+q)(p-q)\).

So the expression becomes

\[
\frac{(p+q)(p^2-pq+q^2)}{3(p^2+pq+q^2)}
\;\times\;
\frac{12}{(p+q)(p-q)}
\;=\;
\frac{12}{3}\;\cdot\;
\frac{(p+q)(p^2-pq+q^2)}{(p^2+pq+q^2)\,(p+q)(p-q)}.
\]

Cancel \(3\) into \(12\) to get \(4\), and cancel the common \((p+q)\):

\[
\boxed{\;
\frac{4\,(p^2-pq+q^2)}{(p^2+pq+q^2)\,(p-q)}
\;,}
\]
with the understanding that \(p\neq\pm q\) so that no denominator vanishes.

To divide, rewrite as a multiplication by the reciprocal and factor everything:

Original:
\[
\frac{\frac{2a^2 - a - 21}{5a + 20}}
     {\frac{a^2 + 7a + 12}{a^2 + 8a + 16}}
\;=\;
\frac{2a^2 - a - 21}{5(a+4)}\;\times\;\frac{(a+4)^2}{(a+3)(a+4)}.
\]

Factor \(2a^2 - a -21=(2a-7)(a+3)\).  Then

\[
\frac{(2a-7)(a+3)}{5(a+4)}
\;\times\;
\frac{(a+4)^2}{(a+3)(a+4)}
\;=\;
\frac{2a-7}{5}
\]

after cancelling \((a+3)\) and the two \((a+4)\).  

Answer:
\[
\boxed{\frac{2a-7}{5}},\quad a\neq -3,\,-4.
\]

